                           <locus target="#126r-129r">-126r-129r</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Summary of basic fiqh rules.</q>
                           <note>Written on ruled paper by different hands, with different inks; folios sewn together with the previous folios</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#33v-34r">-33v-34r</locus>
                           <desc>Glosses</desc>
                           <q>Quotation from al-Buǧayrimī about Miʻrāj and Isrā'.</q>
                           <note>Small piece of paper, sewn together with the others</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#92">-92</locus>
                           <desc>Loose folio</desc>
                           <q>Poorly written words, difficult to understand: بسم الله الرحمن الرحيم أوضعته و...أمينا وضعته حليما ...يمينا رب سما نفي</q>
                           <note>Written in blue ballpoint on a small piece of rules paper</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#129r">-129r</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Note about how to perfom ritual sacrifice of animals; Incipit: هذ بحث الذبح وزكاة كل الحيوان ان قدر عليه بقطع كل الحلقوم والمرء والحلقوم مجر النفس يعني مجراه</q>
                           <note>Written on ruled paper by different hands, with different inks; folios sewn together with the previous folios</note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                           <locus target="#1r-138r">-1r-138r</locus>
                           <desc>Marginalia</desc>
                           <q>Corrections in the margins and notes marked “Baǧīramī”, “Tuḥfa”, “Mawāhib al-ṣamad”, “Iqnā‘”, “šarḥu-hu”, “Fatḥ al-ǧawād”, “Šarqāwī”, “Ibn Qāsim”.</q>
                           <note/>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                           <locus target="#129v">-129v</locus>
                           <desc>Fawā'id and masā'il</desc>
                           <q>Chains of transmission of an unreadable ḥadīṯ.</q>
